
@startuml

package "Smart Home Automation System" {

    "SmartHome" as SH
    "Room" as R
    "SensorDevice" as SD
    "ActuatorDevice" as AD
    "ActivityLog" as AL
    "AutomationRule" as AR
    "RuleTrigger" as RT
    "ControlCommand" as CC
    "SensorReading" as SR

    SH "1" -- "*" R : contains
    R "1" -- "*" SD : contains
    R "1" -- "*" AD : contains
    SD "1" -- "1" SR : generates
    AD "1" -- "1" CC : receives
    AL "1" -- "*" SR : stores
    AL "1" -- "*" CC : stores
    AR "1" -- "1" RT : triggers
    RT "1" -- "*" CC : executes

    note right of SH
        - unique physical address
        - manages rooms and devices
    end note

    note right of R
        - name
        - location within smart home
    end note

    note right of SD
        - device ID
        - type (e.g., temperature, movement)
        - status (active/inactive)
    end note

    note right of AD
        - device ID
        - type (e.g., light, lock)
        - status (active/inactive)
    end note

    note right of AL
        - timestamp
        - log entries (sensor readings, control commands)
    end note

    note right of AR
        - rule ID
        - precondition (Boolean expression)
        - action (sequence of control commands)
        - status (active/inactive)
        - dependencies
        - conflicts
    end note

    note right of RT
        - timestamp
        - triggered rule
        - execution status
    end note

    note right of CC
        - command type (e.g., lockDoor, turnOnHeating)
        - status (requested, completed, failed)
        - timestamp
    end note

    note right of SR
        - sensor ID
        - value
        - timestamp
        - room
    end note

}

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **SmartHome** contains multiple **Rooms**.
- Each **Room** may contain **SensorDevices** and **ActuatorDevices**.
- **SensorDevices** generate **SensorReadings**.
- **ActuatorDevices** receive **ControlCommands**.
- All **SensorReadings** and **ControlCommands** are stored in an **ActivityLog**.
- **AutomationRules** can be triggered by **RuleTriggers**, which record when a rule was executed.
- **RuleTriggers** execute a sequence of **ControlCommands**.
- **AutomationRules** can have dependencies or conflicts with other rules.

